    &lt;/span&gt;        
    
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When we’re learning or exploring,&lt;br&gt;
whether it’s a new skill, a career move,&lt;br&gt;
or simply life itself,&lt;br&gt;
we often crave certainty.&lt;br&gt;
We want a map, a list of steps, a clear destination.&lt;br&gt;
But here’s the paradox:&lt;br&gt;
sometimes, knowing too much holds us back,&lt;br&gt;
while not knowing enough pushes us forward.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
